ulme, M., Jones, P., Representing twentieth century space-time climate variability. Part II: Development of 1901-96 monthly grids of terrestrial surface climate (2000) J. Clim., 13, pp. 2217-2238; Nicholls, N., Lavery, B., Frederiksen, C., Drosdowsky, W., Recent apparent changes in relationships between the El Niñ o-Southern Oscillation and Australian rainfall and temperature (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, pp. 3357-3360; Smith, T.M., Reynolds, R.W., Extended reconstruction of global sea surface temperatures based on COADS data (1854-1997) (2003) J. Clim., 16, pp. 1495-1510; Sobel, A.H., Held, I.M., Bretherton, C.S., The ENSO signal in tropical tropospheric temperature (2002) J. Clim., 15, pp. 2702-2706; Su, H., Neelin, J.D., Teleconnection mechanisms for tropical Pacific descent anomalies during El Niño (2002) J. Atmos. Sci., 59, pp. 2694-2712; Su, H., Neelin, J.D., The scatter in tropical average precipitation anomalies (2003) J. Clim., 16, pp. 3966-3977; Trenberth, K.E., Hurrell, J.E., Comments on: The interpretation of short climate records, with comments on the North Atlantic and Southern Oscillations (1999) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 80, pp. 2721-2722; Wunsch, C., The interpretation of short climate records, with comments on the North Atlantic and Southern Oscillations (1999) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 80, pp. 245-255; Xie, P., Arkin, P.A., Analysis of global monthly precipitation using gauge observations, satellite estimates and numerical model predictions (1996) J. Clim., 9, pp. 840-858","Lyon, B.; Intl. Res. Inst. Climate Prediction, Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory, Columbia University, New York, NY 10964, United States; email: blyon@iri.columbia.edu",,,,,,,,00948276,,GPRLA,,"English","Geophys. Res. Lett.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-13244283009
